China Taiping Insurance Holdings
Co. (966) , which underwrites insurance through its subsidiaries, may
buy a 25 percent stake in Taiping Life Insurance Co. from parent
China Taiping Insurance Group Co.  The company is considering strategic investments which may
be funded by issuing new equity, it said in a statement to the
 Hong Kong  stock exchange today. No agreement has been made on
possible acquisitions, it said. The company doesnâ€™t plan to
issue A shares in China, according to the statement.  Shares in China Taiping will resume trading tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
